' plan-58-A: the POSITIVE fixture, and the A/B boundary marker.
'
' This declaration satisfies every `check_buffer_slots` rule — OUT direction,
' exactly one BUFFER clause, named by RETURN, `List OF Byte` return, a SIZE
' expression over a wrapper parameter. It passes both ctype gates and lowers.
'
' plan-58-A shipped this fixture asserting the opposite: back then the thunk
' REFUSED to lower a CBuffer, because A landed vocabulary and rejection only and
' the marshaling was B's. The golden recorded that refusal, and it flipped to a
' clean build the moment B landed the staging pass — which was the point of
' writing it that way.
'
' Front-end acceptance is all this fixture proves now. The runtime proof that the
' bytes are actually right lives in
' `tests/rt-behavior/native/native-cbuffer-read-rt`, against a real libc.
IMPORT io

LINK "demo" AS demo
  FUNC readBytes(n AS Integer) AS List OF Byte
    SYMBOL "demo_read"
    ABI (buf OUT CBuffer, n CInt64) AS status CInt32
    BUFFER buf SIZE n
    RETURN buf
  END FUNC
END LINK

FUNC main() AS Integer
  ' Calling it is what forces the thunk to be lowered.
  io::print(toString(len(demo::readBytes(16))))
  RETURN 0
END FUNC
